Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. From Romanus Ugwu, Abuja The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has disclosed that a total number of 87.2 million Nigerian electorate will be eligible to exercise their franchise in this weekend’s presidential and National Assembly election. According to the latest breakdown released by the commission at a world press conference held in Abuja ahead the poll thus weekend’s, States like Lagos, Kano, Kaduna, Katsina and Rivers lead the voting strength. While Lagos has 6.214 million voters, Kano, 5.5 million, Kaduna 4.16 million, Katsina, 3.45 million, Rivers, 3.28 million, Ekiti remained the least with 958,052.